Marco Garfagnini has taken up residence at Château de Noirieux installed in the middle of a greennery by the loire river, with beautiful surroundings, manor and château from the 15th and 17th centuries.  
From Tuscany in Italy,Marco Garfagnini proposes healthy eating and well balanced diet.The objective of of Château de Noirieux,near Angers is to preserve the singularity of his cooking and make it his signature.
The culinary  harmony introduced at Noirieux, the flavours of Italy at the heart of the countryside near Angers,brings to mind his glorious career.
A beautiful challenge for this professional that makes his passion the pillar of his culinary art.
Marco proposes menus inspired from traditional cooking in a modern version.A trip between the french riviera and the north of Italy…
Using only the best produce,transformed as little as possible, his cooking offers healthy eating and well balanced dishes exhalting all their freshness.You can find the chefs specialities and creations,roasted prawns with lemon mustard,ricotta cheese raviolis and fresh mint,filet of Jean Dory with caramelized veal juice or chicken filet baked in a salt crust. Among the desserts apple baked with ginger mascarpone cream,milk ice cream or salty butter caramel.Fresh pasta is prepared twice daily and the risottos are prepared to order. « COOKING THAT COMES FROM THE HEART » 

Marco Garfagnini did his international studies between Paris, London and New York (at the famous Bice NYC) and Cleveland. On returning to his native town of Carrare in Italy in 1996,he opened his own restaurant. One year later he gained his first michelin star. Carrare is situated at the foot of the Apuanes Alpes and the frontier of Ligurie, world famous for its white marble.Riche in culinary traditions,a great source of inspiration for Marco Garfagnini.
In 2002 he was among the five finalistes for the «Best Chef of Italy» and in 2005 he was Chef of the Year by the famous italien guide «  Gambero Rosso »  
Remarqued by José Silva general director of the Four Seasons Hotel at Geneva, he joins the famous palace to open the restaurant Ninan. Eight y ears later he integrates the italien restaurant II Lago where he obtained a michelin star in 2013. At the same time he supervises the Izumi kitchen,a japanese fusion restaurant that proposes dishes like Nobu.
In 2014 he rejoins the Four Seasons George V in Paris where he takes the reins of the new mediterranean restaurant The George,where he proposes simple cooking in harmony with the seasons.
If he did not adventure into gastronomy, Marco Garfagnini would probably be musician, his second passion,he is a blues fan and plays the guitar and harmonica and composes his own songs during his free time.
